# PlantPal Core

## Stack
FastAPI (async) · PostgreSQL · SQLAlchemy async · Alembic · Pydantic v2 · pytest · Docker Compose · YAML config

## Layout
- `app/api/` — route handlers only (thin)
- `app/services/` — all business logic
- `app/models/` — SQLAlchemy models
- `app/schemas/` — Pydantic request/response schemas
- `app/core/` — config, database, logging
- `config/` — YAML config files (never secrets)

## Non-negotiables
- Config in YAML (`config/`), secrets in env (`.env.example` only — never commit `.env`)
- Every schema change needs an Alembic migration
- Every feature needs a pytest test in `tests/`
- Use async SQLAlchemy sessions; no sync DB calls in async routes
- Prefer editing existing files over adding abstractions

## Local dev
- Full stack: `make up` → http://localhost:8000/docs
- Desktop Postgres: `python3 -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate && pip install -e ".[dev]"`
- Migrations: `alembic upgrade head` or `make migrate`
